[_Ichthyophonus hoferi_ is a parasite that infects most organs and tissues
of many marine fish. The disease caused is of economic significance,
because epizootics have resulted in mass mortality of commercial fish
species such as Atlantic herring (_Clupea harengus_ L.). Although systemic
infections are lethal, variations in pathogenic effects -- including
myositis, or muscle inflammation -- have been observed, depending upon the
particular isolate of _I. hoferi_ and the host species involved. - Mod.TG]
